1249 
1250  // All of the addXxxOptions take in the name of the option, and a reference to the field of that option
1251  // in the option structure. Depending on the specific type, it may take in a default value, and may
1252  // take in extra options. The addXxxOptions mostly follow the same pattern, so please see addDoubleOption
1253  // for detailed comments.
1254  //
1255  // List options are those that can be an unknown number of elements, and also take in a reference to
1256  // an integer. This integer will be populated with the number of elements of that type unmarshaled.
1257  //
1258  // Array options are those with a fixed number of elements.
1259  //
1260  // List and Array options should also be able to be specified with the string "NONE" indicating that there
1261  // are no elements. This allows the option to be present in a config file but left blank.
1262 
1263  /*!< \brief addDoubleOption creates a config file parser for an option with the given name whose
1264  value can be represented by a su2double.*/
1265 
1266  void addDoubleOption(const string name, su2double & option_field, su2double default_value);
1267 
1268  void addStringOption(const string name, string & option_field, string default_value);
1269 
1270  void addIntegerOption(const string name, int & option_field, int default_value);
1271 
1272  void addUnsignedLongOption(const string name, unsigned long & option_field, unsigned long default_value);
1273 
1274  void addUnsignedShortOption(const string name, unsigned short & option_field, unsigned short default_value);
1275 
1276  void addLongOption(const string name, long & option_field, long default_value);
1277 
1278  void addBoolOption(const string name, bool & option_field, bool default_value);
1279 
1280  // enum types work differently than all of the others because there are a small number of valid
1281  // string entries for the type. One must also provide a list of all the valid strings of that type.
1282  template <class Tenum, class Tfield>
1283  void addEnumOption(const string name, Tfield& option_field, const map<string,Tenum>& enum_map, Tenum default_value);
1284

1461  /*!
1462  * \brief Get reference origin for moment computation.
1463  * \param[in] val_marker - the marker we are monitoring.
1464  * \return Reference origin (in cartesians coordinates) for moment computation.
1465  */
1466  std::array<su2double,3> GetRefOriginMoment(unsigned short val_marker) const {
1467  std::array<su2double,3> RefOriginMoment{{0.0}};
1468  if(val_marker < nMarker_Monitoring) {
1469  RefOriginMoment[0] = RefOriginMoment_X[val_marker];
1470  RefOriginMoment[1] = RefOriginMoment_Y[val_marker];
1471  RefOriginMoment[2] = RefOriginMoment_Z[val_marker];
1472  }
1473  return RefOriginMoment;
1474  }
1475 
1476  /*!
1477  * \brief Get reference origin x-coordinate for moment computation.
1478  * \param[in] val_marker - the marker we are monitoring.

1489

3266  /*!
3267  * \brief Get the tag if the iMarker defined in the geometry file.
3268  * \param[in] val_tag - Value of the tag in which we are interested.
3269  * \return Value of the marker <i>val_marker</i> that is in the geometry file
3270  * for the surface that has the tag.
3271  */
3272  short GetMarker_All_TagBound(string val_tag) {
3273  for (unsigned short iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_All; iMarker++) {
3274  if (val_tag == Marker_All_TagBound[iMarker]) return iMarker;
3275  }
3276  return -1;
3277  }

3666  /*!
3667  * \brief Return true if a fluid solver is in use.
3668  */
3669  bool GetFluidProblem(void) const {
3670  switch (Kind_Solver) {
3671  case MAIN_SOLVER::EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::RANS:
3672  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS:
3673  case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES:
3674  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS:
3675  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS:
3676  return true;
3677  default:
3678  return false;
3679  }
3680  }
3681 
3682  /*!
3683  * \brief Return true if a structural solver is in use.
3684  */
3685  bool GetStructuralProblem(void) const {
3686  return (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY) || (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM);
3687  }
3688 
3689  /*!
3690  * \brief Return true if a heat solver is in use.
3691  */
3692  bool GetHeatProblem(void) const {
3693  return (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::HEAT_EQUATION) || (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_HEAT);
3694  }
3695 
3696  /*!
3697  * \brief Return true if a high order FEM solver is in use.
3698  */
3699  bool GetFEMSolver(void) const {
3700  switch (Kind_Solver) {
3701  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS: case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_LES:
3702  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_NS: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_RANS:
3703  return true;
3704  default:
3705  return false;
3706  }
3707  }
3708 
3709  /*!
3710  * \brief Return true if a NEMO solver is in use.
3711  */
3712  bool GetNEMOProblem(void) const {
3713  switch (Kind_Solver) {
3714  case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES:
3715  return true;
3716  default:
3717  return false;
3718  }
3719  }
3720 
3721  /*!
3722  * \brief Return true if an AUSM method is in use.

3724  bool GetAUSMMethod(void) const {

3726  case UPWIND::AUSM : case UPWIND::AUSMPLUSUP: case UPWIND::AUSMPLUSUP2: case UPWIND::AUSMPWPLUS:
3727  return true;
3728  default:
3729  return false;
3730  }
3731  }
